The OCAML API for Z3 was tested using OCaml 3.09.3.
You also need CamlIDL to be able to generate the OCAML API.

- To download OCaml
  http://caml.inria.fr/ocaml/      

- To download CamlIDL
  http://caml.inria.fr/pub/old_caml_site/camlidl

- To build the OCaml API for Z3
  ./build-lib.sh <OCAMLLIB>

  Example:
  ./build-lib.sh /usr/local/lib/ocaml
        

Acknowledgements:
The OCaml interface for Z3 was written by Jakob Lichtenberg. Many thanks to him!
The script for building OCaml on Linux was written by Ming Kawaguchi. Many thanks to him!

   